
=Bio=

"David is the lead software developer for Arduino, an open-source microcontroller development platform. He’s also a graduate student in Leah Buechley’s High-Low Tech group at the MIT Media Lab, where he investigates tools and processes to help people create interactive objects. He has a master’s degree from the Interaction Design Institute Ivrea and helped to found the Copenhagen Institute of Interaction Design."


